The paper deals with face analysis techniques in the context of human-robot interaction, which suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of 3D modelling and face recognition techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments with face recognition databases, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the mention of a robot system incorporating the framework suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
